{"name":"Illusionary Terrain (figment)","type":"spell","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 1 sp</p><p>You change the qualities of the terrain inside the @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.mkyArd580qQASaQO]{figment}, changing how the ground looks and feels. Any of the ground within the area that you choose becomes difficult terrain.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"10","units":"minute"},"cover":null,"target":{"value":10,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cube"},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"attribute","target":"","amount":1},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"","components":{"vocal":false,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"atwill","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.ydMUY4sNQPdmG5Bs"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685545766859,"modifiedTime":1685549323553,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"9VZgkFKaaYu51YFC"}
{"name":"Obscure (glamer)","type":"spell","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You gain the following @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.jTmvnj5tbm8mRAFD]{glamers}:</p><p><strong>Cost:</strong> 0 sp</p><p>The target becomes blurred, granting disadvantage to any attacks made against them and making them lightly obscured. This effect ends for a target that attacks or casts a spell or sphere ability.</p><p><strong>Augment 1 sp:</strong> The target becomes invisible instead of just blurred for the duration. Anything that the target is wearing or carrying is invisible as long as it remains on the target. The invisibility ends for a target that attacks or casts a spell or sphere ability.</p><p><strong>Augment 1 sp:</strong> The obscure effect does not end if the target attacks or casts a spell or sphere ability.</p><p><strong>Augment 1 sp:</strong> You can muffle the target, removing disadvantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks from the target produced from heavy armor, and give disadvantage on any Wisdom (Perception) checks made to hear the target.</p><p><strong>Augment 0 sp:</strong> If you possess @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.w0uruW7YzHNEANaA]{Greater Illusions}, you can give disadvantage on any Wisdom (Perception) checks made to smell the target.</p><p><strong>Augment 1 sp:</strong> If you possess @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.fSPwuGZDlNgEqvQT]{Veiled Illusions}, you can suppress all auras from the target, such as magical auras from its equipment or its alignment or creature type aura.</p><p><strong>Augment 1 sp:</strong> If you possess @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.w0uruW7YzHNEANaA]{Greater Illusions}, the benefits of obscure apply even to targets with blindsight and tremorsense. If you possess @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.ErCjuJJn3i0ygoaJ]{Intelligent Illusions}, the benefits of obscure apply even to targets with thoughtsense, and hide the target from talents and from divination school spells that read the mind such as @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.ppWAAEul0QHtm4er]{detect thoughts} or magical lie-detection.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"10","units":"minute"},"cover":null,"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"attribute","target":"","amount":0},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"","components":{"vocal":false,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"atwill","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.QkA51Y52D1MHeg28"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685545766859,"modifiedTime":1685548638945,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"AV0NaE0WWB3IgbAH"}
{"name":"Intelligent Illusions (sensory)","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>When augmenting a @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment} to include both an image and sound, you can also grant it intelligence. This means your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment} can fool spells and abilities such as detect thoughts or telepathy and allow them to do quick calculations as if using your Intelligence score. Your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figments} can appropriately act on their own as well, responding to stimuli even if you are not there to direct the illusion yourself. This means you no longer need to use your action to direct your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figments}, although you must still spend an action to give them orders (for example, once you spend your action to order the illusion of a bartender to talk to the patrons, it will continue to do so until you spend another action to give it new orders).</p><p>Additionally, if you give a target the @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.JWtKAjGVFd2g9kw9]{Illusionary Disguise (glamer)}, they can now fool thought-detecting and memory-probing magic, displaying only the mind, memories, and thoughts you desire unless the creature attempting the probe succeeds on a an [[/r 1d20 + @skills.inv.mod]]{Intelligence (Investigation)} check against your sphere DC to notice the thoughts and memories are not truly genuine.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Illusion Sphere","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.3HmcLdSfVmmEoj0K"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685546688375,"modifiedTime":1685548391358,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"ErCjuJJn3i0ygoaJ"}
{"name":"Insistent Illusions","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Augment 1 sp:</strong> Choose one creature you can perceive. You give that target disadvantage on their next Intelligence (Investigation) check made to examine or disbelieve this @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment}, made within the next minute.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Illusion Sphere","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.3HmcLdSfVmmEoj0K"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685546688375,"modifiedTime":1685548387157,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"FviiIS09r0j3f3nA"}
{"name":"Shadow Infusion","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Whenever you use a @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment} to deal psychic damage, you can change the damage type to any other damage type.</p><p><strong>Augment 1 sp:</strong> Any or all creatures within your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment} are grappled as you choose until they successfully disbelieve the figment. A creature grappled by your illusion can make a free [[/r 1d20 + @skills.inv.mod]]{Intelligence (Investigation)} check each round to disbelieve your illusion.</p><p><strong>Augment 3 sp:</strong> Any or all creatures within your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment} are restrained as you choose until they successfully disbelieve the @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment}. A creature restrained by your illusion can make a free [[/r 1d20 + @skills.inv.mod]]{Intelligence (Investigation)} check each round to disbelieve your illusion.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Illusion Sphere (Greater Illusions, Potent Illusions), Level 5","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.3HmcLdSfVmmEoj0K"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685546688375,"modifiedTime":1685548396863,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"HvLULNB9GQ2ApmgH"}
{"name":"Illusionary Disguise (glamer)","type":"spell","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 1 sp</p><p>You can create a @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.jTmvnj5tbm8mRAFD]{glamer} that changes a target’s appearance. This can change the appearance of an object, or alter a creature to seem 1 foot shorter or taller, make it appear thin, fat, or in between, or change its apparent species, gender, outfit, etc.. You can’t change the target’s body type, so you must adopt a form that has the same basic arrangement of limbs.</p><p>Otherwise, the extent of the illusion is up to you. This @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.jTmvnj5tbm8mRAFD]{glamer} only disguises the target’s appearance and voice, but can extend to their smell and taste if you have @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.w0uruW7YzHNEANaA]{Greater Illusions}, their magic auras if you possess @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.fSPwuGZDlNgEqvQT]{Veiled Illusions}, or even their minds if you have @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.ErCjuJJn3i0ygoaJ]{Intelligent Illusions}.</p><p>Just as with a @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment}, the changes are not real; if a target attempts to interact with the illusion (for example, pick up an illusionary hat on top of your head), they pass right through it and feel your hair. Also, just as with a @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.items.IBhDAr7WkhWPYLVn]{disguise kit}, a creature can use its action to inspect your Appearance and attempt an [[/r 1d20 + @skills.inv.mod]]{Intelligence (Investigation)} check to see through the disguise (against your spell save DC). While these actions can cause a target to disbelieve the disguise, unlike with @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figments}, disbelieving does not automatically let them see through the disguise.</p><p><strong>Augment 1 sp:</strong> If you possess @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.w0uruW7YzHNEANaA]{Greater Illusions}, you can give your illusionary disguise a tactile component; interacting with the illusion does not reveal the deception, although your illusion still does not have substance (thus, feeling the hat on top of your head wouldn’t make the target disbelieve, but they still could not pick it up off your head).</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"10","units":"minute"},"cover":null,"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"attribute","target":"","amount":1},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"","components":{"vocal":false,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"atwill","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.yR6GSqbIaT69o5Lh"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685545766859,"modifiedTime":1685548521512,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"JWtKAjGVFd2g9kw9"}
{"name":"Imageless","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You cannot create @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figments} (except for <strong>obstructions</strong> through @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.wTn9TBv4zWrYMewS]{Illusionary Obstruction}). You gain one <strong>(glamer)</strong> talent or @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.wTn9TBv4zWrYMewS]{Illusionary Obstruction} as a bonus talent.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Illusion Sphere","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.3HmcLdSfVmmEoj0K"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685546688375,"modifiedTime":1685548840326,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"LCizKfB4RncVO67z"}
{"name":"Illusionary Terrain","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Augment 0 sp:</strong> You can create @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figments} that alter the appearance of the terrain itself or other features of the area around you. For example, while you could previously cover a wall with a bigger wall or use an illusionary carpet to hide a pit, now you can use a <strong>figment</strong> that makes a wall of fire appear as a harmless wall of mist, or change the appearance of terrain from grassland to forest. Extreme changes (such as changing a warm grassland into a wintery tundra) may require additional <strong>(sensory)</strong> talents to be convincing.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Illusion Sphere","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.3HmcLdSfVmmEoj0K"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685546688375,"modifiedTime":1685548170008,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"O360V6fx9efGruaw"}
{"name":"Programmed Illusion","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Augment 1 sp:</strong> When creating a @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment}, you can cause it not to appear immediately, but instead to wait to activate when a specific condition occurs. The illusion is imperceptible until then. The trigger can be as general or detailed as you like, though it must be based on visual or audible conditions that occur within 30 feet of the @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment’s} location. For example, you could create an illusionary monster that appears when someone opens a door, or a message that appears written in the air when someone says the correct word or phrase.</p><p>Your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment} has a permanent duration until triggered or dispelled (though you must still concentrate, unless using the augment to allow it to endure without concentration), though once triggered it performs a predetermined set of actions (set by you when it is created) with a maximum duration of 5 minutes, after which the @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment} disappears and the effect ends. If this @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment} is also altered with @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.PfQPf43D65fMuDop]{Permanent Illusion}, then it will reset after 5 minutes, activating again the next time it’s trigger happens.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Illusion Sphere","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.3HmcLdSfVmmEoj0K"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685546688375,"modifiedTime":1685548707045,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"PJp25hTavc57wRO4"}
{"name":"Permanent Illusion","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your illusions are long lasting.</p><p><strong>Augment 4 sp:</strong> Your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figments} and @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.jTmvnj5tbm8mRAFD]{glamers} last until dispelled, without requiring your concentration.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Illusion Sphere, Universal sphere (Extended (metasphere)), Level 11","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.3HmcLdSfVmmEoj0K"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685546688375,"modifiedTime":1685548395852,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"PfQPf43D65fMuDop"}
{"name":"Selective Illusions","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can designate creatures to automatically disbelieve your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figments}, or to be immune to <strong>(figment)</strong> or <strong>(glamer)</strong> talents you use.</p><p><strong>Augment 0 sp:</strong> You can choose to have a total number of creatures equal to your proficiency bonus([[@prof]]) automatically disbelieve or be immune to this illusion.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Illusion Sphere","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.3HmcLdSfVmmEoj0K"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685546688375,"modifiedTime":1685548388976,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"TEflC8o1F2xAiBkR"}
{"name":"Mirage","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Augment 2 sp:</strong> When using @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.O360V6fx9efGruaw]{Illusionary Terrain}, you can increase the @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment} size to a 1-mile cube.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Illusion Sphere (Illusionary Terrain), Level 11","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.3HmcLdSfVmmEoj0K"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685546688375,"modifiedTime":1685548394888,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Ue1SKqUBVmFNJ3CF"}
{"name":"Complex Illusions","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Augment 1 sp:</strong> You can split your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figments} into multiple independent illusions. Whenever you use your action to control a <strong>figment</strong>, you can control all of your <strong>figments</strong> with the same action. For example, instead of creating a dinner party with a single <strong>figment</strong> (in which case all of the guests and the table would need to be contained within your <strong>figment’s</strong> size), you could create one <strong>figment</strong> for the table and another <strong>figment</strong> for each guest, each of which could move independently within your illusion range.</p><p>You can create up to three <strong>figments</strong>, but each one can only be half the size of your usual <strong>figments</strong>. The number of <strong>figments</strong> you can create increases at 5th level (four figments), 11th level (five figments), and 17th level (six figments).</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Illusion Sphere","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.3HmcLdSfVmmEoj0K"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685546688375,"modifiedTime":1685548376504,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"WQFEsG1PPa3ncy5a"}
{"name":"Control Figment","type":"spell","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can make a [[/r 1d20 + @mod]]{spellcasting} ability check against the spell save DC or sphere DC of the controller of an existing @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.illusion.b1XgEOuW7gWwNPPR]{figment}. If successful, you gain control of the <strong>figment</strong> and may command it as if it was your effect. Treat the <strong>figment</strong> in all ways as if it was cast by you, except this does not change any of the original variables related to level, Illusion sphere talents, class abilities, or <strong>spell points</strong>. You however must remain within your illusion range of the <strong>figment</strong> to maintain this effect as normal. If the <strong>figment</strong> was being maintained by concentration, you must assume concentration over the effect as if you had cast it.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"attribute","target":"","amount":0},"ability":"","actionType":"rsak","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"","components":{"vocal":false,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"atwill","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2SHuUW1t6696PefF.Item.yBwSol9PTXqxkhJE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":16855